  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get JWT Token (Client Credentials)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set('jwt_token', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('token_expires_in', jsonData.expires_in || 3600);",
                  "    pm.test('JWT Token obtained successfully', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.access_token).to.exist;",
                  "    });",
                  "    console.log('✅ JWT Token saved to {{jwt_token}}');",
                  "    console.log('Token expires in:', jsonData.expires_in, 'seconds');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    pm.test('Failed to get JWT token', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect.fail('Could not obtain token: ' + pm.response.status + ' - ' + pm.response.text());",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "client_credentials",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{client_secret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_url}}/realms/{{keycloak_realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_url}}"],
              "path": ["realms", "{{keycloak_realm}}", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Get a JWT access token from Keycloak using client credentials flow (DEV environment).\n\n**Setup Required:**\n1. Load .env.notify-dev.json as environment\n2. Set Keycloak environment variables:\n   - `keycloak_url`: Keycloak instance URL\n   - `client_id`: Your OAuth2 client ID\n   - `client_secret`: Your OAuth2 client secret\n\nThe token will be automatically saved to `{{jwt_token}}` for use in API requests."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get OAuth2 Token (Kong - Local)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set('jwt_token', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('token_expires_in', jsonData.expires_in || 3600);",
                  "    pm.test('OAuth2 Token obtained successfully', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.access_token).to.exist;",
                  "    });",
                  "    console.log('✅ OAuth2 Token saved to {{jwt_token}}');",
                  "    console.log('Token type:', jsonData.token_type);",
                  "    console.log('Token expires in:', jsonData.expires_in, 'seconds');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    pm.test('Failed to get OAuth2 token', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect.fail('Could not obtain token: ' + pm.response.status + ' - ' + pm.response.text());",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "client_credentials",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{client_secret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "scope",
                  "value": "notify",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kong_token_url}}",
              "host": ["{{kong_token_url}}"]
            },
            "description": "Get an OAuth2 access token from Kong's OAuth2 plugin (DEV environment with Kong).\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n1. Kong is running in DEV environment\n2. Load .env.notify-dev.json as environment\n3. Set kong_token_url environment variable\n4. Kong seed script has created test credentials\n\n**Default Test Credentials (from kong-seed.sh):**\n- Client A: client_id=test-client-a, secret=test-client-secret-a-12345678901234567890\n- Client B: client_id=test-client-b, secret=test-client-secret-b-98765432109876543210\n- Client C: client_id=test-client-c, secret=test-client-secret-c-11111111111111111111\n\nThe token will be automatically saved to `{{jwt_token}}` for use in API requests."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Frontend OAuth2 Token (Standard Realm - Interactive Login)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set('frontend_jwt_token', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('frontend_token_expires_in', jsonData.expires_in || 3600);",
                  "    pm.test('Frontend OAuth2 Token obtained successfully', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.access_token).to.exist;",
                  "    });",
                  "    console.log('✅ Frontend OAuth2 Token saved to {{frontend_jwt_token}}');",
                  "    console.log('Token type:', jsonData.token_type);",
                  "    console.log('Token expires in:', jsonData.expires_in, 'seconds');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    pm.test('Failed to get Frontend OAuth2 token', function() {",
                  "        pm.expect.fail('Could not obtain token: ' + pm.response.status + ' - ' + pm.response.text());",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "authorization_code",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{frontend_client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{frontend_client_secret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "redirect_uri",
                  "value": "{{frontend_redirect_uri}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "code",
                  "value": "{{authorization_code}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_url}}/auth/realms/standard/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "realms", "standard", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Exchange authorization code for OAuth2 access token from Keycloak frontend realm (standard).\n\n**Setup Required:**\n1. First, navigate to Keycloak authorization endpoint in browser:\n   `{{keycloak_url}}/realms/standard/protocol/openid-connect/auth?client_id={{frontend_client_id}}&redirect_uri={{frontend_redirect_uri}}&response_type=code&scope=openid+profile+email`\n2. Login with your BC Government credentials\n3. Copy the authorization code from the redirect URL\n4. Set `authorization_code` environment variable with the code\n5. Run this request to exchange it for an access token\n\n**Environment Variables Required:**\n- `keycloak_url`: Keycloak instance URL (e.g., https://test.loginproxy.gov.bc.ca)\n- `frontend_client_id`: Frontend OAuth2 client ID (e.g., notify-6388)\n- `frontend_client_secret`: Frontend OAuth2 client secret\n- `frontend_redirect_uri`: Redirect URI for OAuth2 callback (e.g., http://localhost:3000/callback)\n- `authorization_code`: Authorization code obtained from Keycloak login\n\nThe token will be automatically saved to `{{frontend_jwt_token}}` for use in frontend API requests."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
